  | I did some network performance tests to see how good pasta is compared to slirp4netns. I start on one physical machine nginx (as podman container), and send requests from other phyiscal mashine with "Apache HTTP server benchmarking tool" (ab). Here the results:<br>**_Default rootless network (pasta)_**<br>`ab -c 1 -n 10000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   5.885 seconds<br>Requests per second:    1699.26 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.588 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.588 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 4 -n 40000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   4.498 seconds<br>Requests per second:    8893.57 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.450 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.112 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 8 -n 80000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   5.775 seconds<br>Requests per second:    13851.79 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.578 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.072 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 16 -n 160000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   11.197 seconds<br>Requests per second:    14289.42 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       1.120 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.070 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 32 -n 320000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   21.100 seconds<br>Requests per second:    15165.95 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       2.110 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.066 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>**_Rootless network with slirp4netns_**<br>`ab -c 1 -n 10000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   8.713 seconds<br>Requests per second:    1147.76 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.871 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.871 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 4 -n 40000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   7.143 seconds<br>Requests per second:    5600.11 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.714 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.179 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 8 -n 80000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   5.745 seconds<br>Requests per second:    13924.88 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.575 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.072 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 16 -n 160000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   6.438 seconds<br>Requests per second:    24852.06 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.644 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.040 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 32 -n 320000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   11.061 seconds<br>Requests per second:    28930.86 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       1.106 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.035 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>**_Default rootfull network_**<br>`ab -c 1 -n 10000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   5.074 seconds<br>Requests per second:    1970.86 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.507 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.507 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 4 -n 40000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   4.779 seconds<br>Requests per second:    8369.89 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.478 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.119 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 8 -n 80000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   4.174 seconds<br>Requests per second:    19165.58 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.417 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.052 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 16 -n 160000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   5.182 seconds<br>Requests per second:    30878.20 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.518 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.032 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>`ab -c 32 -n 320000`<br>```<br>Time taken for tests:   8.508 seconds<br>Requests per second:    37610.08 [#/sec] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.851 [ms] (mean)<br>Time per request:       0.027 [ms] (mean, across all concurrent requests)<br>```<br>**_Conclusion_**<br>As you can see, pasta performs better than slirp4netns only up to a certain parallelism (specifically up to 8). Then slirp4netns starts to perform significantly better. Rootfull network scales best, which is to be expected.<br>**_Question_**<br>Are there any options to improve pasta's scalability? |
  
